There is no question i probably wouldn't answer truthfully. NO matter how embarissing it will be to me. I figure i answer it and if you realy know me you will understand and if you don't then oh well. I have nothing to hide even if some times it may not be the best thing i have done or said i did it for a reason. Wether i was being fun or mad or scared or even crazy. I do things i do for reason and for the most part i do not regret much. I know who i am and i know in the end i'll look back and laugh and still be happy. People don't all ways like other that have nothing to hide. Often times being an open book leaves me to get hurt easy or i say too much about others and i hurt people. I don't mean to i don't do it on purpose but i figure if i have nothing to hide you should have nothing to hide. I guess some people just like things to be private. Anyways this is my last public post the rest will be for me only. I'm getting older and trying to move forward is hard when you all ways look back. I have to let go and start over i often lose my self in groups. It sad when your new friends say "i wonder what you were like before"  i guess i notice i'm not the same and i just want to be me.
